everythingIsTheBest sells out (Ultimate Xtreme SF Limited Edition)
Dustin went
The pendulum always comes back around, right? Only a year ago we wrested our souls back from the clutches of the great beast, but today we find ourselves right back where we started. Soulless shells of human beings, we are enslaved for a googol years. But, the upside is that we got paid fat and can throw some seriously killer parties. Come out in San Francisco on Friday for a celebration of success, and excess. It's been a phenomenal year and we all deserve to celebrate. ** Now on Saturday at Space Gallery! The downstairs bar and entrance will be closed at midnight, so please try to show up before then! **
Saturday, December 18, 2010 at 8:00pm - Sunday, December 19, 2010 at 4:00am in UTC
Space Gallery,1141 Polk Street,San Francisco,California,United States

The Go Game
Dustin went
Hey all. With paintball out of the way, it's time to start thinking about our next e team event -- The Go Game. What is The Go Game? Nobody knows, because it's different every time. We will be embarking on a magical journey of fun, puzzles, team building in downtown Palo Alto, all customized around Facebook and our engineering experience. From http://www.thegogame.com "The Go Game is the future of corporate play. It's the intersection of wireless technology, Mission: Impossible, and team building as you have never seen it. Take your company to new levels of creativity and cohesiveness with the next generation of team building activities. Since our launch in March 2002, we've made superheros out of companies like Microsoft, Verizon, and Toyota. Find out how you can get in on the game." * The Go Game goes down on October 29th. * The Go Game will start in the 164 Cafe, going from 1pm – 5:30 and will end with judging and drinks/food at Old Pro. * The actual events will be all around Palo Alto. * Prizes! of nontrivial monetary value will be awarded to the winning team. Make sure to RSVP, and check the website if you want more details. But mostly, strap yourselves in because it's going to be a wild ride!!!!!!!!!!!!
Wednesday, October 29, 2008, 1 PM - 6 PM in PDT
Downtown PA,Palo Alto,California,United States
